  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The eightfold Koph. Fidelity to God's word, and deliverance according to His promise, is the purport of his unceasing prayer. Even in the morning twilight (נשׁף) he was awake praying. It is not הנּשׁף, I anticipated the twilight; nor is קדּמתּי, according to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 89:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", equivalent to קדמתיך, but ואשׁוּע...קדּמתּי is the resolution of the otherwise customary construction קדמתי לשׁוּע, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jonah 4:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", inasmuch as קדּם may signify \"to go before\" (",
